WEBVTT

00:01.227 --> 00:02.409
<i> Previously on</i>
<i> "Our Kind of People"...</i>

00:02.411 --> 00:03.727
You and Angela
have something going, right?

00:03.729 --> 00:04.911
I might've
messed that up.

00:04.913 --> 00:06.321
She's got her ex
hanging around.

00:06.323 --> 00:08.415
I love you.
<i> Aww, I'll catch you</i>
<i> soon, okay?</i>

00:08.417 --> 00:09.657
I got to break up
with her.

00:09.659 --> 00:11.068
Mommy?

00:11.070 --> 00:13.012
Rose
was my dearest friend.

00:13.014 --> 00:15.514
Leah:
When you told me to torpedo
her Graceties membership,

00:15.516 --> 00:17.832
you destroyed us becoming
real sisters.

00:17.834 --> 00:21.520
Angela: Piggy turned herself in
for murdering Darius Bates.

00:21.522 --> 00:23.522
Leave Oak Bluffs,
and I will help Piggy

00:23.524 --> 00:26.083
and set up seed money
for Eve's Crown.

00:26.085 --> 00:27.192
Darius?

00:27.194 --> 00:28.585
Teddy gave it
to him to hide

00:28.587 --> 00:30.178
the night that
your mother was arrested.

00:30.180 --> 00:32.865
Get ready, Teddy,
'cause I'm coming for you.

00:32.867 --> 00:34.925
♪♪

00:34.927 --> 00:36.184
Piggy:
Alright, no peeking.

00:36.186 --> 00:38.945
Now sit your precious booty
all the way down.

00:38.947 --> 00:40.614
Alright.

00:40.616 --> 00:42.599
Open!
What is this?

00:42.601 --> 00:45.527
This is my new line --
Nikki's Halo.

00:45.529 --> 00:47.529
Named after
the most precious,

00:47.531 --> 00:49.864
beautiful, sweetest angel
in my life.

00:49.866 --> 00:52.459
[ Laughs ] Mom!
I know we're
shutting down the store

00:52.461 --> 00:55.962
and moving out of the Bluffs,
but I wanted to remind you

00:55.964 --> 00:58.782
of everything you've
accomplished this summer...

00:58.784 --> 01:00.784
Mm-hmm.
...how far you've come.

01:00.786 --> 01:03.386
I am so proud of you.

01:04.456 --> 01:06.231
Thank you, Mom,
but -- but you know

01:06.233 --> 01:09.068
all of these doors opened
because of<i> you.</i>

01:09.070 --> 01:10.552
Like, I -- Look at me.

01:10.554 --> 01:14.239
I'm a debutante,
and I'm in love, and...

01:14.241 --> 01:15.723
Ohh.
[ Laughter ]

01:15.725 --> 01:18.468
And my life changed
because you had the courage

01:18.470 --> 01:19.820
to come here
and start all of this.

01:19.822 --> 01:23.064
Yeah, you say that sitting
in the middle of my closed shop.

01:23.066 --> 01:24.232
Oh, hush.

01:24.234 --> 01:26.418
You had a big summer,
too.

01:26.420 --> 01:29.329
Look,
you opened Eve's Crown.

01:29.331 --> 01:32.649
You did right
by your mama.

01:32.651 --> 01:34.259
You didn't get the deal
that you wanted,

01:34.261 --> 01:38.555
but, Ange,
you got so much more.

01:39.491 --> 01:40.748
[ Laughs ]

01:40.750 --> 01:42.434
I'm gonna go
post all of these.

01:42.436 --> 01:43.844
You do that.

01:43.846 --> 01:45.104
[ Sighs ]

01:45.106 --> 01:47.940
I am proud, but I just
can't stop thinking

01:47.942 --> 01:49.924
about what was stolen
from Mama.

01:49.926 --> 01:51.852
I know that gun
Darius gave you

01:51.854 --> 01:53.353
has something to do
with her.

01:53.355 --> 01:54.780
I think if I could
just talk to Leah --

01:54.782 --> 01:56.598
Angela,
I know we want to get Teddy,

01:56.600 --> 01:58.766
but I feel bad enough
that you agreed

01:58.768 --> 02:00.619
to leave town
on account of me.

02:00.621 --> 02:03.455
You need that seed money
that Teddy promised you

02:03.457 --> 02:06.441
so you can take Eve's Crown
to the next level.

02:06.443 --> 02:09.019
If your father finds out
we are still poking around

02:09.021 --> 02:11.021
in his secrets,
he'll renege,

02:11.023 --> 02:13.373
and, baby, you will just
walk away with nothing.

02:13.375 --> 02:15.359
I ain't worried
about him, okay?

02:15.361 --> 02:17.619
Mama is watching over me.
I know that.

02:17.621 --> 02:20.455
Now, listen,
Nikki has one Deb event left

02:20.457 --> 02:23.700
at the Grand Illumination Ball,
which means I have two days

02:23.702 --> 02:25.051
to clear Mama's name.

02:25.053 --> 02:28.296
And then we'll leave the island
for good.

02:28.298 --> 02:31.132
♪ Our kind of people ♪

02:31.134 --> 02:34.561
♪ Ooh, ooh ♪

02:34.563 --> 02:38.157
♪♪

02:39.401 --> 02:41.827
♪ Trying to see
the good in you ♪

02:41.829 --> 02:44.054
♪ Brought out the bad in me ♪

02:44.056 --> 02:46.331
♪ Always giving the benefit
of the doubt ♪

02:46.333 --> 02:48.483
♪ Put my energy in a drought ♪

02:48.485 --> 02:51.837
[ Clears throat ]
♪ Is that really asking
too much? ♪

02:51.839 --> 02:54.840
Wow. Well, there was a time
when the sight of me in a towel

02:54.842 --> 02:56.750
would at least get
a "Hey, now."

02:56.752 --> 02:59.827
Still reading the note
that your mother left you?

02:59.829 --> 03:02.014
She was this
Graceties chapter's

03:02.016 --> 03:05.242
most revered president.

03:05.244 --> 03:06.668
What have I done
as president?

03:06.670 --> 03:09.930
I voted against my sister
to keep some secret for Daddy

03:09.932 --> 03:11.748
that he won't even
tell me about.

03:11.750 --> 03:12.916
It was shady.

03:12.918 --> 03:14.676
Angela once told me
that we were two sides

03:14.678 --> 03:16.028
of the same coin.

03:16.030 --> 03:18.088
I just never suspected
that I was the side

03:18.090 --> 03:19.531
that was facing down
towards the gutter.

03:19.533 --> 03:21.091
No, hey, stop, stop.

03:21.093 --> 03:23.443
You're being too hard
on yourself.

03:23.445 --> 03:25.278
You remember what we used
to tell the twins

03:25.280 --> 03:26.705
when they were babies?

03:26.707 --> 03:28.373
They would drop a snack on the
floor and they just sat there

03:28.375 --> 03:31.210
and they would cry and cry
and cry and cry.

03:31.212 --> 03:33.453
Pick it up and
"kiss it up to God."
That's right.

03:33.455 --> 03:36.715
If you pick up your
mistake fast enough, you
hold it up to the sky,

03:36.717 --> 03:39.218
all the bad
will be undone.

03:39.220 --> 03:40.219
Mm.

03:40.221 --> 03:42.946
Sweetheart,
everything can be fixed.

03:42.948 --> 03:50.804
♪♪

03:50.806 --> 03:53.623
I'll have those plans for you
by the end of the week.

03:53.625 --> 03:54.624
Excellent.

03:54.626 --> 03:56.526
I'm really looking forward
to that.

04:00.132 --> 04:02.557
Ah. How's Leah faring
this morning?

04:02.559 --> 04:04.317
Grieving.

04:04.319 --> 04:07.579
Feeling guilty for helping you
run her sister out of town --

04:07.581 --> 04:10.415
the same sister that was
supporting her at the funeral.

04:10.417 --> 04:11.975
Do not fret.

04:11.977 --> 04:13.977
Angela and I have made a deal
that benefits both of us.

04:13.979 --> 04:16.997
As for Leah, we're holding
a press conference this morning

04:16.999 --> 04:19.649
which is bound
to lift her spirits.

04:19.651 --> 04:23.153
Franklin Holdings is announcing
that we are back in the black.

04:23.155 --> 04:24.488
Congratulations, Teddy.

04:24.490 --> 04:25.597
Thank you.

04:25.599 --> 04:27.582
We're also announcing
that Franklin Holdings

04:27.584 --> 04:31.011
has permanently acquired
Darmon Foods.

04:31.013 --> 04:32.604
You senile now, too,
Teddy?

04:32.606 --> 04:36.108
Clear enough to know it's a bad
day to be Raymond Dupont.

04:36.110 --> 04:38.560
I've recently hired
a private investigator

04:38.562 --> 04:41.855
to look into Jack's
"accidental" death.

04:41.857 --> 04:43.931
Now, he informed me
that Jack was seen

04:43.933 --> 04:46.359
giving the key card
to his room --

04:46.361 --> 04:49.029
the room where
he was found dead --

04:49.031 --> 04:50.289
to Leah.

04:50.291 --> 04:51.939
You put my daughter
in the position

04:51.941 --> 04:53.850
where she was seeking comfort
outside of her marriage,

04:53.852 --> 04:56.295
which is further proof
that you are undeserving of her

04:56.297 --> 04:59.447
and unfit to step in
as patriarch.

04:59.449 --> 05:01.224
Right, I-I see,
because the man

05:01.226 --> 05:04.285
who cheated on his wife
and had an illegitimate child,

05:04.287 --> 05:05.953
who he's also running
out of town --

05:05.955 --> 05:08.289
that man, he's fit.
Mm-hmm.

05:08.291 --> 05:10.809
I haven't, as of yet,
spoken to the police,

05:10.811 --> 05:14.295
as you had the case closed
so quickly,

05:14.297 --> 05:19.209
but my PI also told me
that a few members saw you

05:19.211 --> 05:21.227
enter Jack's room
the day of his death.

05:21.229 --> 05:24.156
Now, I'm sure the police would
find that very interesting.

05:24.158 --> 05:27.826
And despite any
previous misconceptions,

05:27.828 --> 05:30.662
I am taking back
Mr. Harmon's shares.

05:30.664 --> 05:34.499
So, as I said, bad day
to be Raymond Dupont.

05:34.501 --> 05:40.005
♪♪

05:40.007 --> 05:43.157
Nikki: I can't believe
the Ball is in two days.

05:43.159 --> 05:45.251
I've been meaning to say
thank you to you guys

05:45.253 --> 05:48.496
for holding me down
since my grandmother...

05:48.498 --> 05:49.422
well, passed.

05:49.424 --> 05:51.165
I wouldn't have been
anywhere else.

05:51.167 --> 05:54.094
Losing my grandma
was one of the toughest things

05:54.096 --> 05:55.261
I've ever been through,

05:55.263 --> 05:57.430
but having Mama Eve
up in heaven

05:57.432 --> 05:59.340
is like having
a guardian angel.

05:59.342 --> 06:01.935
Like, she guided us here
to the Bluffs,

06:01.937 --> 06:05.922
and now I have
Nate and Taylor.

06:05.924 --> 06:09.684
And I-I didn't know
how dope it was to have cousins.

06:09.686 --> 06:11.352
Whatever Grandma Rose
is planning up there,

06:11.354 --> 06:13.763
I'm sure it's incredible.

06:13.765 --> 06:15.207
I like that.
Thank you.

06:15.209 --> 06:18.526
Well, since I only have a couple
more days of beach living left,

06:18.528 --> 06:21.195
I'm gonna go do that
quicksand thing with my toes.

06:21.197 --> 06:23.465
[ Laughs ] Okay.

06:27.370 --> 06:30.296
I can't keep acting
like everything is cool.

06:30.298 --> 06:31.631
I know,
but it's just --

06:31.633 --> 06:33.408
I don't think that
this is the right time

06:33.410 --> 06:34.634
to tell her that
we're back together.

06:34.636 --> 06:36.970
She deserves to have
a good end to the summer.

06:36.972 --> 06:38.897
Taylor!

06:38.899 --> 06:40.649
Come here!

06:42.051 --> 06:43.568
Right.
Come on.

06:43.570 --> 06:49.633
♪♪

06:49.635 --> 06:51.576
[ Laughter ]

06:51.578 --> 06:55.822
♪♪

06:55.824 --> 07:00.660
Thanks for coming over
and for coming to the funeral.

07:00.662 --> 07:02.754
I wanted to be there
for you,

07:02.756 --> 07:04.089
and I was hoping
we could talk.

07:04.091 --> 07:05.331
Yeah, of course,

07:05.333 --> 07:08.242
but first,
I have a surprise for you.

07:09.245 --> 07:11.245
Thank you, everyone,
for making the time

07:11.247 --> 07:13.657
for this emergency meeting
of the Graceties.

07:13.659 --> 07:15.600
What is this?
[ Sighs ]

07:15.602 --> 07:18.328
The other day,
I made an error in judgment

07:18.330 --> 07:21.940
when I cast a down vote
for Angela Vaughn's membership.

07:21.942 --> 07:23.942
This summer,
Angela has brought

07:23.944 --> 07:26.169
a fresh perspective
to our group.

07:26.171 --> 07:28.947
I mean, from the very beginning,
she showed her value

07:28.949 --> 07:31.341
when she saved
our fashion show.

07:31.343 --> 07:32.509
I mean, many of our alumni

07:32.511 --> 07:35.178
are very impressed
with her tenacity.

07:35.180 --> 07:37.956
You called us all together
for this?

07:37.958 --> 07:40.366
According to the bylaws,

07:40.368 --> 07:44.688
the only way to revisit
a down vote

07:44.690 --> 07:48.208
is if the senior member
of the chapter

07:48.210 --> 07:50.360
grants an exception.

07:50.362 --> 07:53.196
I am the senior member
of the chapter.

07:53.198 --> 07:55.882
Which is why you are here
so that we can discuss --

07:55.884 --> 07:58.201
Madame President...
No, no, no, no.
Come on, come on.

07:58.203 --> 08:02.797
...you keep spitting in the face
of well-worn tradition --

08:02.799 --> 08:06.726
allowing girls to escort girls
to the Cotillion.

08:06.728 --> 08:10.489
And now you're trying
to shoehorn<i> your</i> candidate

08:10.491 --> 08:14.217
into the club
to suit your own whims.

08:14.219 --> 08:17.387
This isn't about whims.
It's about what's right.

08:17.389 --> 08:20.314
Alright, a few of us
have been talking,

08:20.316 --> 08:25.562
and we realize that you are
understandably emotional.

08:25.564 --> 08:26.730
But we also realize

08:26.732 --> 08:30.008
that it is clearly affecting
your leadership.

08:30.010 --> 08:33.494
If you don't think that
you can uphold the rules

08:33.496 --> 08:35.421
of this chapter
as its president,

08:35.423 --> 08:37.331
then perhaps you'd like
to take a seat

08:37.333 --> 08:41.594
and hand over the biggest
event of the summer

08:41.596 --> 08:43.337
to someone
we can trust.

08:43.339 --> 08:45.840
Those rules are antiquated
and you know it.

08:45.842 --> 08:48.175
Your mother believed
in those rules,

08:48.177 --> 08:51.029
and I am not
going to dance

08:51.031 --> 08:55.108
on my friend Rose's grave
and change them now.

08:55.110 --> 08:58.519
Keep my mother's name
out of your mouth.

08:58.521 --> 08:59.779
Olivia, try me!

08:59.781 --> 09:03.783
No, she -- she is --
she is a spiteful old bitch.

09:03.785 --> 09:05.710
This is your
grief talking, okay?

09:05.712 --> 09:07.862
I've been there.
I've lived it.

09:07.864 --> 09:10.531
You can throw this Ball
in your sleep,

09:10.533 --> 09:11.991
and I'll help you.

09:11.993 --> 09:16.388
But right now, just chill
and do what you do best.

09:16.390 --> 09:21.893
♪♪

09:21.895 --> 09:24.229
For those of you
who are in doubt,

09:24.231 --> 09:26.731
let me make this
very clear --

09:26.733 --> 09:28.958
I will not be
"taking a seat."

09:28.960 --> 09:31.961
I'm the president
of this chapter,

09:31.963 --> 09:33.387
and this Grand Illumination
Ball's

09:33.389 --> 09:35.799
gonna be the best one ever --

09:35.801 --> 09:38.468
for my mother,
for her legacy.

09:38.470 --> 09:40.061
So dress to impress,
ladies,

09:40.063 --> 09:42.229
because the bar
just got real high.

09:42.231 --> 09:43.990
Meeting adjourned.

09:43.992 --> 09:49.129
♪♪

09:53.501 --> 09:55.819
Well, I don't understand --
why does Angela still need

09:55.821 --> 09:56.928
to leave town?

09:57.155 --> 09:59.246
You said it was Angela digging
that could hurt Mommy.

09:59.248 --> 10:00.340
Well, Mommy's gone.

10:00.342 --> 10:01.433
As patriarch of this family,

10:01.435 --> 10:03.009
do me a favor
and just let it go.

10:03.011 --> 10:05.328
Angela was there for you
through your heart attack.

10:05.330 --> 10:08.164
She has been there for me more
times than she needed to be.

10:08.166 --> 10:09.849
And, you know,
just to let her walk away

10:09.851 --> 10:12.518
without saying anything
is shameful...

10:12.520 --> 10:14.354
and the opposite
of a patriarch.

10:14.356 --> 10:16.281
-Mr. Franklin.
-Mr. Franklin!

10:16.283 --> 10:17.857
Hello, hello, everyone.

10:17.859 --> 10:20.452
[ Reporters
shouting indistinctly ]

10:20.454 --> 10:22.621
Thank you all
for joining us today

10:22.623 --> 10:25.031
<i> for the opening</i>
<i> of the Louis Franklin Stadium.</i>

10:25.033 --> 10:28.701
And I would like to give
a special shout-out

10:28.703 --> 10:31.020
to a family who became
one of Franklin's

10:31.022 --> 10:33.356
highest-performing
acquisitions

10:33.358 --> 10:34.966
at the stadium's
concession stand

10:34.968 --> 10:37.694
by featuring
an all-beef hot dog

10:37.696 --> 10:42.031
with mustard and sweet relish
and sauerkraut --

10:42.033 --> 10:44.476
<i> the "Dupont Dog."</i>

10:44.478 --> 10:46.478
[<i> Chuckles</i> ]

10:47.539 --> 10:49.314
Dupont Dog.
[ Chuckles weakly ]

10:49.316 --> 10:50.631
I don't think so.

10:50.633 --> 10:52.651
Aside from hot dogs,
the Louis Franklin Stadium

10:52.653 --> 10:56.729
will be offering
American luxury, affordability,

10:56.731 --> 10:58.064
<i> and the best damn team</i>

10:58.066 --> 11:00.550
<i> that this country</i>
<i> has ever seen.</i>

11:00.552 --> 11:02.327
<i> So, King James,</i>
<i> watch out for your throne,</i>

11:02.329 --> 11:03.328
<i> 'cause we're coming</i>
<i> for your crown.</i>

11:03.330 --> 11:04.478
[ TV shuts off ]
Shut up.

11:04.480 --> 11:05.980
He thinks he's
so untouchable

11:05.982 --> 11:07.666
just 'cause he has money
and power.

11:07.668 --> 11:10.151
I asked you over here

11:10.153 --> 11:11.561
'cause I need your help,

11:11.563 --> 11:14.255
and I think I have
something on Teddy.

11:16.902 --> 11:18.492
Darius gave that
to Piggy.

11:18.494 --> 11:20.011
We think it has something
to do with the night

11:20.013 --> 11:21.237
my mother was arrested.

11:21.239 --> 11:23.256
I think it's connected
to Teddy.

11:23.258 --> 11:25.458
Now, I know your dad
worked for him.

11:25.460 --> 11:27.260
Is it possible
that he bought it?

11:27.262 --> 11:29.020
Could there be paperwork
in his stuff?

11:29.022 --> 11:30.930
I know it's hard going
through those things, but --

11:30.932 --> 11:32.432
No, no.
I wanna help you.

11:32.434 --> 11:34.508
I'll -- I'll get
to looking ASAP.

11:34.510 --> 11:35.527
Thank you.

11:35.529 --> 11:38.029
So, I hear you're moving
back to Boston?

11:38.031 --> 11:41.682
I've been trying
to figure out how to tell you.

11:41.684 --> 11:43.350
Angela, I'm --
Piggy:
Sorry to interrupt,

11:43.352 --> 11:45.019
but you need
to see this, Ange.

11:45.021 --> 11:46.871
I've been doing
research on the web

11:46.873 --> 11:49.949
for newspaper clippings
from '84 and found out

11:49.951 --> 11:52.101
that Teddy's brother Louis
was killed

11:52.103 --> 11:55.104
the same night
as the Grand Illumination Ball.

11:55.106 --> 11:56.272
Shot in the head.

11:56.274 --> 11:57.531
The case was never solved,

11:57.533 --> 11:59.459
and apparently,
he was very vocal

11:59.461 --> 12:01.886
about the drug problem
in Edgartown

12:01.888 --> 12:03.555
and was working
to clean up the area.

12:03.557 --> 12:05.557
I remember Teddy saying
that when he died,

12:05.559 --> 12:06.799
they weren't on good terms.

12:06.801 --> 12:08.727
Well, my dad collected rents
for the apartments

12:08.729 --> 12:09.877
he owned over there.

12:09.879 --> 12:11.454
Some of them were
known crack houses.

12:11.456 --> 12:12.789
It would have been easy
for Teddy

12:12.791 --> 12:13.881
to plant that stash
on Eve.

12:13.883 --> 12:15.233
Well, you better be
damn sure

12:15.235 --> 12:16.459
if you're gonna put
Teddy Franklin on blast.

12:16.461 --> 12:18.311
He could take it out
on Angela.

12:18.313 --> 12:20.071
I would never put Angela
in danger like that.

12:20.073 --> 12:21.555
Oh, trust me, I know.

12:21.557 --> 12:24.300
And that is exactly why we're
leaving here tomorrow night.

12:24.302 --> 12:25.910
♪♪

12:25.912 --> 12:28.246
I'll see what I can find.
Angela: Thank you.

12:28.248 --> 12:36.996
♪♪

12:36.998 --> 12:39.649
Nikki: I was thinking
you could come to Boston

12:39.651 --> 12:40.759
for winter break.

12:40.761 --> 12:42.485
You know, we could
go ice skating

12:42.487 --> 12:44.596
and we could watch
Debbie Allen's

12:44.598 --> 12:47.015
"Hot Chocolate Nutcracker."

12:48.493 --> 12:50.251
Yeah.

12:50.253 --> 12:52.103
Nikki, can we talk?

12:55.442 --> 12:56.691
We're breaking up?

12:59.671 --> 13:02.763
We're breaking up.

13:02.765 --> 13:03.856
Why?

13:03.858 --> 13:06.451
It's...the end of summer,

13:06.453 --> 13:09.362
and you're going
back to Boston.

13:09.364 --> 13:12.698
Taylor, I -- W-We can --
We can do long-distance.

13:12.700 --> 13:14.459
I wanna make this work.

13:14.461 --> 13:17.778
I love you.

13:17.780 --> 13:19.547
You don't love me?

13:20.616 --> 13:22.783
You can't even say it.

13:22.785 --> 13:24.118
So, what?
I-I was just something

13:24.120 --> 13:25.878
to make your summer
more interesting?

13:25.880 --> 13:27.380
You were bored,
or something?
No, Nikki,
it's not like that.

13:27.382 --> 13:28.956
You just wanted something
to play with?

13:28.958 --> 13:30.383
No.
Then what is it like?
What is it like, Taylor?

13:30.385 --> 13:33.019
We were frien--
Tell me what it's like!

13:34.039 --> 13:35.388
Are you serious?

13:36.541 --> 13:39.150
As if falling off a yacht
and telling the police

13:39.152 --> 13:42.654
your girlfriend pushed you
wasn't excitement enough.

13:43.639 --> 13:45.548
I hate you.
I wish I --

13:45.550 --> 13:47.492
I wish I never met you.
[ Sniffles ]

13:47.494 --> 13:51.287
♪♪

13:54.726 --> 13:57.502
Nate:
So, what kind of garlic bread?
I mean, how do you make it?

13:57.504 --> 13:59.062
You say you like --
you want garlic bread

13:59.064 --> 14:00.505
like you got a problem
with the toast I make.

14:00.507 --> 14:02.398
Yeah, because it's toast.
I'm talking about the garlic --

14:02.400 --> 14:03.842
You okay?

14:03.844 --> 14:05.159
No.

14:05.161 --> 14:06.736
Taylor broke up with me.

14:06.738 --> 14:07.846
Oh.

14:08.073 --> 14:10.907
I told her I loved her
and I wanted to fight for us

14:10.909 --> 14:12.166
'cause she's, like,
the first person

14:12.168 --> 14:14.168
I've ever really loved.

14:14.170 --> 14:15.578
I feel really stupid.

14:15.580 --> 14:17.430
Nate: I would have done
the same thing, baby girl.

14:17.432 --> 14:20.108
You have to really fight
for your first love.

14:21.769 --> 14:24.103
Can we just not go to
the Grand Illumination Ball?

14:24.105 --> 14:26.255
It's not like you got inducted
to the Graceties.

14:26.257 --> 14:28.366
I just really feel like
I can't see her again.

14:28.368 --> 14:30.017
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
But you know what?

14:30.019 --> 14:31.944
I know it may not
feel like this right now,

14:31.946 --> 14:35.356
but...you're gonna
love again.

14:35.358 --> 14:37.524
You're gonna feel
the butterflies again.

14:37.526 --> 14:38.451
You think so?

14:38.453 --> 14:40.027
I know so.

14:40.029 --> 14:43.456
You know, Mother used to say
that if, uh, you take a noodle,

14:43.458 --> 14:45.441
close your eyes, throw it over
your back onto the wall,

14:45.443 --> 14:48.869
whatever shape it makes is the
first initial of your next.

14:48.871 --> 14:51.297
Yeah, and your
other grandmother

14:51.299 --> 14:53.725
also got married five times
before she died,

14:53.727 --> 14:55.059
so she would know.
[ Laughs ]

14:55.061 --> 14:57.395
Five is a lot of times.
[ Laughter ]

14:57.397 --> 14:59.455
But, like --
Okay, I don't know

14:59.457 --> 15:00.306
if Mom told you,
but I'm bi,

15:00.308 --> 15:01.974
so I probably need
two noodles.

15:01.976 --> 15:04.143
Like, so, it goes over
the shoulder like that?

15:04.145 --> 15:06.220
And the other one goes like --
Oh, it goes like that.

15:06.222 --> 15:08.072
Whaaaat?
[ Chuckles ]

15:08.074 --> 15:09.073
Oh, ho, ho.

15:09.075 --> 15:12.410
Your daughter just...

15:12.412 --> 15:14.561
Ahh!
Ahh!

15:14.563 --> 15:16.730
Nate!
[ Laughter ]

15:16.732 --> 15:17.916
Stop it right now!

15:18.067 --> 15:19.992
Wait, wait, wait, wait!
Okay, okay, okay, okay.

15:19.994 --> 15:21.586
I'm just kidding.
Here we go.
Hey, no!

15:21.588 --> 15:22.979
[ Laughter ]

15:22.981 --> 15:24.923
I'm so happy
to see you smiling.

15:24.925 --> 15:28.409
Honey, you don't know
how life is gonna end up.

15:28.411 --> 15:32.746
I had no idea that he would ever
come back into our lives,

15:32.748 --> 15:35.541
but love is powerful...

15:35.543 --> 15:38.252
and it never dies.

15:38.254 --> 15:41.164
It just changes form,
like energy.

15:41.166 --> 15:42.999
Like Mama Eve.

15:43.001 --> 15:44.609
Like Mama Eve.

15:44.611 --> 15:47.111
♪ Funny how you acting
brand new ♪

15:47.113 --> 15:49.280
♪ I still feel a way ♪

15:53.027 --> 15:54.619
<i> Why you filmin' me</i>
<i> while I'm workin'?</i>

15:54.621 --> 15:56.937
Nate:<i> Babe, this is your first</i>
<i> hairpiece.</i>

15:56.939 --> 15:58.347
<i> I'm trying</i>
<i> to capture history.</i>

15:58.349 --> 16:00.274
<i> Say something.</i>
You remember that day?

16:00.276 --> 16:02.460
What?
I was so proud of you.

16:02.462 --> 16:03.795
<i> Ready?</i>

16:03.797 --> 16:06.464
Oh, my gosh.

16:06.466 --> 16:10.802
<i> Hi, I'm Angie,</i>
<i> and my hair company,</i>

16:10.804 --> 16:14.864
<i> Eve's Crown, is about to be</i>
<i> the bomb empire, okay?</i>

16:14.866 --> 16:16.365
<i> You heard it here first.</i>

16:16.367 --> 16:18.625
[<i> Laughs</i> ]<i> That's it!</i>

16:18.627 --> 16:21.795
Yep. You rolled around
with that camcorder,

16:21.797 --> 16:23.630
trying to be the next Spike.
<i> Alright, turn it off.</i>

16:23.632 --> 16:26.559
You and all that smacking.
<i> Stop playing!</i>

16:26.561 --> 16:28.561
[ Beeps ]

16:28.563 --> 16:29.729
What is this?

16:29.731 --> 16:32.381
Uh -- Look at you.

16:32.383 --> 16:35.234
So, is this why you made
my favorite --

16:35.236 --> 16:36.719
[ Gasps ] Stop.

16:36.721 --> 16:40.832
This is that cheap wine we used
to drink back in the day.

16:40.834 --> 16:42.074
What is this?

16:42.076 --> 16:44.651
This was the night
I had planned 17 years ago

16:44.653 --> 16:45.819
for my first love.

16:45.821 --> 16:47.747
Then my screw-up made us
have to hit pause

16:47.749 --> 16:50.675
on something
that was amazing.

16:52.846 --> 16:55.162
But tonight...

16:55.164 --> 16:56.663
I want us to hit play.

16:57.500 --> 17:00.351
So you're not really
losing anything

17:00.353 --> 17:02.595
by leaving here,
Angela.

17:02.597 --> 17:06.441
You're walking into a plan
that we've always had.

17:07.510 --> 17:10.028
I want us to have
a second chance.

17:10.030 --> 17:13.514
But not just us --
let's give Nikki a family.

17:13.516 --> 17:16.016
Nate, w-what?

17:16.018 --> 17:18.161
[ Laughs ] What?

17:20.765 --> 17:22.540
[ Gate latch clicks ]

17:23.877 --> 17:25.025
[ Sighs ]

17:25.027 --> 17:26.769
♪♪

17:26.771 --> 17:28.120
Brother, do you mind?

17:28.122 --> 17:29.380
Actually, I do.

17:29.382 --> 17:31.049
But, Angela,
I have some news

17:31.051 --> 17:33.134
that might help
clear your mother's name.

17:36.464 --> 17:37.764
Do your thing.

17:46.066 --> 17:50.476
Um...
I didn't answer him.

17:50.478 --> 17:53.629
He's just, you know,
offering a life

17:53.631 --> 17:57.800
that Nikki would love
and thrive in, and...

17:57.802 --> 18:00.820
I'm sorry. I shouldn't even be
talking to you like that.

18:00.822 --> 18:03.730
I'm just so used
to confiding in you.

18:03.732 --> 18:05.308
You've been there for me.

18:05.310 --> 18:07.585
You taught me to float,

18:07.587 --> 18:08.994
and that's the only reason
I've been able

18:08.996 --> 18:10.496
to make it through
all this.

18:10.498 --> 18:12.498
Angela,
I want you to be happy --

18:12.500 --> 18:14.834
whatever that looks like
for you.

18:14.836 --> 18:17.911
But part of that
is finding the truth

18:17.913 --> 18:20.264
about Teddy
and your mother.

18:20.266 --> 18:21.841
Look, you --
you were right.

18:21.843 --> 18:23.659
My pops purchased
that gun for Teddy.

18:23.661 --> 18:25.511
I used my contacts
at the police department,

18:25.513 --> 18:27.847
and I was able to get
Louis' autopsy report.

18:27.849 --> 18:31.258
Now, the bullet that killed
Louis matches Teddy's gun.

18:31.260 --> 18:36.030
So...Teddy may have actually
killed his own brother?

18:37.283 --> 18:39.617
Maybe Mama Eve was a --
a witness.

18:39.619 --> 18:41.268
Maybe that's why he was
trying to shut her up.

18:41.270 --> 18:44.013
Well, it says here,
Louis' estimated time of death

18:44.015 --> 18:46.940
was between
10:00 and 11:30,

18:46.942 --> 18:49.293
when the Illumination Ball
would have been in full swing.

18:49.295 --> 18:51.036
Now, all we need to do
is find out

18:51.038 --> 18:53.522
if Teddy ever was missing
from the Ball.

18:53.524 --> 18:56.025
You know what?
I got a pile of --

18:56.027 --> 18:58.194
of Graceties photos
from Leah.

18:58.196 --> 19:01.139
I can put together
a visual timeline, you know?

19:01.141 --> 19:03.532
I can --
We're close to finding
answers.

19:03.534 --> 19:05.368
Now, you haven't,
but if you asked me

19:05.370 --> 19:07.536
if you should stand down
and run away with him

19:07.538 --> 19:10.130
or stay here and fight
for answers...

19:11.133 --> 19:15.394
...my opinion is biased,
but I vote for you to stay.

19:15.396 --> 19:22.718
♪♪

19:22.720 --> 19:24.996
[ Gate latch clicks ]

19:28.726 --> 19:31.060
♪ Roll it, roll it,
roll it up one time ♪

19:31.062 --> 19:34.488
♪ Why your lovin'
always gets me high? ♪

19:34.490 --> 19:35.506
[ Sighs ]

19:35.508 --> 19:37.066
♪ I'm so confused ♪

19:37.068 --> 19:39.343
♪ Why do you do this to me
every time? ♪

19:39.345 --> 19:41.470
I really hate
that Nikki got hurt.

19:42.515 --> 19:43.681
Was she okay?

19:43.683 --> 19:46.684
♪ Exposing feelings
that I try to hide ♪

19:46.686 --> 19:49.094
I mean, she's upset.

19:49.096 --> 19:51.338
And I get it.

19:51.340 --> 19:53.006
She was like
collateral damage

19:53.008 --> 19:55.526
when we were getting
our stuff together.

19:56.938 --> 19:59.513
[ Sighs ] I don't know.
I hate it.

19:59.515 --> 20:01.515
Yeah. Me, too.

20:01.517 --> 20:04.777
But I'm also happy
we figured our stuff out.

20:04.779 --> 20:07.688
Out of respect for her,
I'm gonna wait till she's gone,

20:07.690 --> 20:10.282
but...when she is,

20:10.284 --> 20:11.951
I'm gonna tell the world
that we're together.

20:11.953 --> 20:13.452
♪ Let's take off
these handcuffs ♪

20:13.454 --> 20:15.862
[ Chuckles ]
You know I'd like that.

20:15.864 --> 20:18.216
♪ Look what you do ♪

20:18.218 --> 20:19.533
Ooh.

20:19.535 --> 20:21.293
I like this, too.

20:21.295 --> 20:24.296
I got it
to remember the summer.

20:24.298 --> 20:26.131
I may have gotten you
one to match.

20:26.133 --> 20:28.300
What? [ Chuckles ]

20:28.302 --> 20:29.227
♪♪

20:29.229 --> 20:30.895
Oh.
[ Chuckles ]

20:30.897 --> 20:31.971
Okay.

20:31.973 --> 20:36.049
♪♪

20:36.051 --> 20:37.884
Someone's been boosting
stuff from my room,

20:37.886 --> 20:39.570
and I know exactly
who it is.

20:39.572 --> 20:41.072
[ Door opens ]

20:44.410 --> 20:47.653
You know...
I had it in my head

20:47.655 --> 20:50.639
that you two were hooking up
behind my back.

20:50.641 --> 20:52.324
But I said, "No.

20:52.326 --> 20:54.994
Quincy wouldn't
disrespect me."

20:54.996 --> 20:57.830
Then I have to hear
the truth from Lauren?

20:57.832 --> 21:01.908
You, young lady,
are leaving this house A.S.A.P.

21:01.910 --> 21:03.319
Ms. Jackie,
you can't do that.

21:03.321 --> 21:04.595
I love Sloane.
[ Scoffs ]

21:04.597 --> 21:06.171
Grandma, please.

21:07.158 --> 21:09.008
Lauren also told me
that several items

21:09.010 --> 21:10.993
have gone missing
from her room.

21:10.995 --> 21:14.480
Your time in this house
is done.

21:18.111 --> 21:21.261
I am sick of your sister
projecting on me

21:21.263 --> 21:22.613
when she's the thief
up in here.

21:22.615 --> 21:24.264
She stole Taylor
from Nikki.

21:24.266 --> 21:27.285
They've been hooking up
behind your cousin's
back for weeks now.

21:27.287 --> 21:34.292
♪♪

21:34.294 --> 21:35.684
Mm.

21:35.686 --> 21:37.628
Angela, I love this idea
of blowing up the pictures

21:37.630 --> 21:39.964
of the past
Illumination Balls.
Right?

21:39.966 --> 21:42.333
I mean, because this needs
to be spectacular.

21:42.335 --> 21:45.027
Yep, for Rose.
[ Chuckles ]

21:45.029 --> 21:46.862
Why don't we pull

21:46.864 --> 21:49.807
all the photos
of Teddy and Rose?

21:49.809 --> 21:51.809
It could be like
a tribute to your moms.

21:51.811 --> 21:53.202
Oh, wow, you know what?

21:53.204 --> 21:54.720
Actually, there's a picture
of them in front

21:54.722 --> 21:56.797
of the Boston House.
You know what?

21:56.799 --> 21:58.891
I'll take the coffee
in my office.

22:00.153 --> 22:04.822
Angela, despite the fact
that I've asked you to leave,

22:04.824 --> 22:07.825
I loved knowing you
and Nikki,

22:07.827 --> 22:11.554
and I thought I should come
and say goodbye --

22:11.556 --> 22:14.498
and say I'm sorry...

22:14.500 --> 22:17.393
about what happened
between me and your mother.

22:17.395 --> 22:21.747
♪♪

22:21.749 --> 22:24.508
Okay, now, I know --
I know you don't understand...

22:25.661 --> 22:27.845
He's just trying
to protect his family.

22:27.847 --> 22:28.995
Listen to me.

22:28.997 --> 22:31.498
He killed
his brother Louis.

22:31.500 --> 22:32.591
What?

22:32.593 --> 22:34.093
No, my uncle was shot
by a drug dealer.

22:34.095 --> 22:36.354
That was Teddy's story.
The case was never solved.

22:36.356 --> 22:37.763
My father loved
my Uncle Louis.

22:37.765 --> 22:40.583
He's naming the stadium
after him, for God's sakes.

22:40.585 --> 22:42.101
[ Scoffs ]
This is why y'all need

22:42.103 --> 22:43.361
a Grand Illumination Ball --

22:43.363 --> 22:45.437
'cause you don't
see anything.

22:45.439 --> 22:47.089
I have the gun.

22:47.091 --> 22:50.368
Teddy was protecting himself,
not Rose.

22:50.370 --> 22:52.778
He hid behind
your mother's mental break

22:52.780 --> 22:55.522
to prevent anyone
from poking into the past.

22:55.524 --> 22:57.449
I have been
looking for evidence

22:57.451 --> 22:59.210
that he left the Ball
that night.

22:59.212 --> 23:02.362
Now, whatever he did had to do
with Louis and Mama Eve.

23:02.364 --> 23:05.091
Okay,
just stop talking.

23:06.611 --> 23:08.611
If you're right...

23:08.613 --> 23:11.055
I lose both of my parents
in a week.

23:11.966 --> 23:14.299
I've already lost
both of mine.

23:14.301 --> 23:17.377
And we are never gonna
get past this.

23:17.379 --> 23:19.397
You will always
choose Teddy,

23:19.399 --> 23:23.109
and I will always
choose my mother.

23:24.887 --> 23:26.237
As long
as that's the case,

23:26.239 --> 23:28.388
then I don't see
how we can be sisters.

23:28.390 --> 23:34.153
♪♪

23:34.155 --> 23:38.082
And I brought it all to Leah.
She won't see it.

23:38.084 --> 23:39.992
She can't? She don't want to?
I don't know.

23:39.994 --> 23:42.311
She's -- Her whole existence
is wrapped up

23:42.313 --> 23:44.663
in being Teddy Franklin's
daughter -- his heir.

23:44.665 --> 23:47.091
Well, she doesn't
know herself like you do.

23:47.093 --> 23:50.428
[ Scoffs ]
That's one of the things
I love about you.

23:50.430 --> 23:53.455
You know, I-I bought this beach
a couple of years ago

23:53.457 --> 23:54.932
because I wanted
to build a house on it,

23:54.934 --> 23:56.842
but I couldn't
get the plans right.

23:56.844 --> 23:58.844
There was always
something missing.

23:59.997 --> 24:03.274
Angela, I can't be
in the same room with you

24:03.276 --> 24:05.425
without wanting
to hold you.

24:05.427 --> 24:06.852
[ Chuckles ]
When you look at me,

24:06.854 --> 24:09.354
my chest gets tight
and I can't breathe.

24:09.356 --> 24:10.522
[ Chuckles ]

24:10.524 --> 24:12.098
Look, I know that
you just got Nate

24:12.100 --> 24:14.100
back in your life,
and that's a good thing.

24:14.102 --> 24:15.953
You -- You have a history
and a daughter,

24:15.955 --> 24:20.032
and I don't wanna get
in between that, but...

24:20.034 --> 24:22.460
Nate is your past.

24:22.462 --> 24:24.353
I'm your present
and your future.

24:24.355 --> 24:28.799
[ Laughs ] What?
♪ Move your intuition,
girl, you love ♪

24:28.801 --> 24:33.028
Angela, I now know what was
missing from those plans.

24:33.030 --> 24:34.029
♪ Ohhhhhhh ♪

24:34.031 --> 24:36.381
A cabinet for rosewater
and honey,

24:36.383 --> 24:39.051
a pool for floating,
a room for Nikki,

24:39.053 --> 24:40.536
but most importantly...

24:40.538 --> 24:43.630
♪ Real men don't come
from right around the corner ♪

24:43.632 --> 24:44.707
...you.

24:44.709 --> 24:47.318
Now, you already have
an Eve's Crown,

24:47.320 --> 24:49.061
but how about
an Angela's Crown?

24:49.063 --> 24:51.046
[ Gasps ]
A home right here
on this beach.

24:51.048 --> 24:53.565
Please, allow me
to build that for you.

24:53.567 --> 24:55.809
♪♪

24:55.811 --> 24:57.236
I j--

24:57.238 --> 25:00.239
[ Sighs,
inhales deeply ]

25:00.241 --> 25:02.725
I just need a moment
to think.

25:02.727 --> 25:05.728
I know. I'm throwing
a lot at you right now, so...

25:05.730 --> 25:08.230
♪ Real men don't come
from right around the corner ♪

25:08.232 --> 25:09.898
...I will see you
at the Ball.

25:09.900 --> 25:12.510
♪♪

25:12.512 --> 25:15.546
♪ You've got decisions ♪

25:15.548 --> 25:21.101
♪♪

25:24.915 --> 25:29.935
♪♪

25:29.937 --> 25:31.695
♪ Alright ♪
♪ I want it all ♪

25:31.697 --> 25:33.589
♪ Gimme, gimme all you got ♪

25:33.591 --> 25:34.548
♪ Baby, I want it all ♪

25:34.550 --> 25:36.108
Remember our first party
this summer?

25:36.110 --> 25:38.427
We had to squeeze in
on Josephine's invite.

25:38.429 --> 25:41.263
And now we are walking in
the front door.

25:41.265 --> 25:44.099
Look how far
you've come, baby.

25:44.101 --> 25:45.960
[ Laughter ]
Mm.

25:46.771 --> 25:48.128
[ Door closes ]

25:49.440 --> 25:51.774
Hey, Nikki, I-I --
Can I go first?

25:51.776 --> 25:53.942
Um, I said some
messed-up things,

25:53.944 --> 25:55.611
and I'm sorry.

25:55.613 --> 25:59.281
I didn't wanna lose you,
I-I still don't,

25:59.283 --> 26:02.451
but someone told me that
love doesn't just disappear.

26:02.453 --> 26:05.045
It's powerful,
so it just changes form.

26:05.047 --> 26:07.898
So, maybe we can
just be friends.

26:07.900 --> 26:10.959
Quincy: You had no right
to tell Jackie anything.
Lauren: Oh, my gosh.

26:10.961 --> 26:12.795
I feel like you're looking
for an apology,

26:12.797 --> 26:13.979
but I'm not sorry.

26:13.981 --> 26:15.631
Sloane is a gold-digger,
and you're a mark.

26:15.633 --> 26:17.299
Are you serious?!
Do you hear yourself right now?!

26:17.301 --> 26:18.801
Hey, hey!
Lower your voices.

26:18.803 --> 26:21.728
Sloane doesn't belong here.
She's a parasite and a liar.

26:21.730 --> 26:23.155
You would know about
being a liar!

26:23.157 --> 26:24.564
You've been hooking up
with Taylor behind Nikki's back

26:24.566 --> 26:26.125
for, what, weeks now?

26:27.995 --> 26:30.162
Nikki, I didn't mean
for you to hear that.

26:30.164 --> 26:31.404
You could've told me.

26:31.406 --> 26:32.906
Lauren: I asked her
to lie to you.

26:32.908 --> 26:34.650
Nikki, I was really just
trying to protect you.

26:34.652 --> 26:36.743
Lies don't help, Lauren.

26:36.745 --> 26:38.078
Can't you see that?

26:38.080 --> 26:40.155
No, 'cause the --
the great Franklin-Duponts,

26:40.157 --> 26:42.749
you just can't help yourselves,
can you?

26:42.751 --> 26:45.510
You're all so cruel.

26:45.512 --> 26:47.830
You just have cruelty
running in your blood,

26:47.832 --> 26:50.182
and I wish
I didn't have any of it

26:50.184 --> 26:51.942
running in my veins.

26:51.944 --> 26:56.171
♪♪

26:56.173 --> 26:58.598
Maybe she's right.

26:58.600 --> 27:00.342
Maybe it's in our blood.

27:00.344 --> 27:04.346
♪♪

27:04.348 --> 27:05.605
Now they're lying
to each other?

27:05.607 --> 27:07.958
I mean, why does this
keep happening?

27:07.960 --> 27:09.793
Okay, Leah, I need you
to listen to me

27:09.795 --> 27:12.020
and finally hear me,
okay?

27:12.022 --> 27:13.797
This is your
father's influence.

27:13.799 --> 27:15.524
Despite what we teach,
our kids have learned

27:15.526 --> 27:17.301
to play chess
and deal in the gray.

27:17.303 --> 27:19.878
He drills it into them
like he's drilled it into you.

27:19.880 --> 27:23.641
This might
cost a lot, but...

27:23.643 --> 27:24.475
you're right.

27:24.477 --> 27:26.385
This dysfunction
has to stop.

27:26.387 --> 27:28.962
The only way
to beat my father

27:28.964 --> 27:31.631
is to take away the thing
he values most --

27:31.633 --> 27:33.333
his legacy.

27:33.335 --> 27:34.393
I just hope
it's not too late

27:34.395 --> 27:37.821
to kiss our whole family
up to God.

27:37.823 --> 27:43.643
♪♪

27:43.645 --> 27:49.574
♪♪

27:49.576 --> 27:50.751
Hello.

27:55.749 --> 27:57.841
I would like
to welcome everyone

27:57.843 --> 28:00.326
to the event
that ends our summer --

28:00.328 --> 28:02.571
our Grand Illumination Ball.

28:02.573 --> 28:04.973
[ Applause ]

28:07.169 --> 28:10.128
My mother loved
the Grand Illumination Ball

28:10.130 --> 28:11.355
for all that it represented.

28:11.357 --> 28:14.174
As the longtime Gracetie
chapter president,

28:14.176 --> 28:17.861
Rose was the light
that guided this group of women

28:17.863 --> 28:19.604
on their path.

28:19.606 --> 28:24.609
So in honor of Rose, the group
would like to present a gift

28:24.611 --> 28:27.262
from the night
that she was first inducted

28:27.264 --> 28:29.689
into the Graceties in 1984,

28:29.691 --> 28:31.875
to her husband...

28:31.877 --> 28:33.026
Teddy Franklin.

28:33.028 --> 28:34.436
[ Chuckles ]

28:34.438 --> 28:37.363
[ Applause ]

28:37.365 --> 28:38.757
Well...

28:40.869 --> 28:43.128
You can't hide
from the truth.

28:43.130 --> 28:44.963
Not anymore, Daddy.

28:44.965 --> 28:53.880
♪♪

28:53.882 --> 28:56.291
I'm sorry.
This is very emotional.

28:56.293 --> 28:58.310
If you would just
give us a minute.

28:58.312 --> 29:01.129
♪♪

29:01.131 --> 29:03.498
[ Breathing heavily ]

29:03.500 --> 29:09.395
♪♪

29:09.397 --> 29:11.139
No, no. Get that
away from me.

29:11.141 --> 29:12.657
[ Box thuds ]
Daddy, I need answers,

29:12.659 --> 29:14.659
so you're gonna tell me
exactly what happened

29:14.661 --> 29:18.422
the night of the
Grand Illumination Ball in 1984.

29:18.424 --> 29:20.090
Angela: You know what?
Let me help you out.

29:20.092 --> 29:22.818
On that night,
Teddy and Rose showed up

29:22.820 --> 29:24.503
at the house
of Darius Bates.

29:24.505 --> 29:26.096
Used to cover up
his dirty work.

29:26.098 --> 29:28.932
Teddy asked him
to hide a gun that night --

29:28.934 --> 29:30.692
that gun right there.

29:30.694 --> 29:33.512
According to Darius,
Rose was mumbling something

29:33.514 --> 29:34.830
about my mother.

29:34.832 --> 29:36.681
I --
Tyrique:
And don't lie, Teddy.

29:36.683 --> 29:38.424
That gun carries
the same type of bullet

29:38.426 --> 29:39.592
that killed your brother
Louis.

29:39.594 --> 29:41.427
Raymond: And at the time
of his death --

29:41.429 --> 29:43.005
the night of the Ball --
your brother Louis

29:43.007 --> 29:45.616
was very unhappy with your
business dealings in Edgartown.

29:45.618 --> 29:48.510
Lauren: Granddaddy,
what are they saying?

29:48.512 --> 29:49.995
Granddaddy?

29:57.354 --> 30:00.872
I loved Eve...
very deeply.

30:00.874 --> 30:04.042
We were gonna meet at
the dock that night
and run away together.

30:04.044 --> 30:07.529
But before she could get there,
Louis showed up,

30:07.531 --> 30:11.457
and we argued
about my new business dealings.

30:11.459 --> 30:13.201
And while we were
at each other's throats,

30:13.203 --> 30:18.482
I hadn't noticed
that Rose followed me.

30:19.968 --> 30:22.394
She was...

30:22.396 --> 30:24.880
manic.

30:24.882 --> 30:26.214
Angry.

30:26.233 --> 30:30.385
She wanted to shoot me,
and she pulled the trigger,

30:30.387 --> 30:32.478
and Louis [voice breaking]
jumped in front...

30:32.480 --> 30:35.223
♪♪

30:35.225 --> 30:37.893
His life for mine.

30:37.895 --> 30:41.063
♪♪

30:41.065 --> 30:44.591
Rose was never the same,
and neither was I.

30:46.253 --> 30:51.598
Ever since, I have felt nothing
but guilt and shame.

30:54.745 --> 30:57.003
[ Sobbing ] I am so sorry.

30:57.005 --> 31:02.058
♪♪

31:02.060 --> 31:05.362
Angela, I was not there
for your mother.

31:05.364 --> 31:09.032
I did what I could,
but I didn't set her up.

31:09.943 --> 31:12.594
My biggest mistake
in life...

31:12.596 --> 31:14.872
[ Exhales sharply ]

31:14.874 --> 31:18.959
...was that I loved the right
woman at the wrong time.

31:19.620 --> 31:21.378
I chose Eve,

31:21.380 --> 31:24.364
and Rose paid the price
for my choice.

31:24.366 --> 31:29.961
♪♪

31:29.963 --> 31:34.466
So I stayed --
to help Rose and you --

31:34.468 --> 31:38.544
and I let go
of my life with Eve.

31:38.546 --> 31:45.569
♪♪

31:45.571 --> 31:48.405
Who set up my mother?

31:48.407 --> 31:50.890
I don't know...

31:50.892 --> 31:53.893
how those drugs
got into her possession.

31:53.895 --> 31:56.896
I...

31:56.898 --> 31:58.898
It's always been
a mystery to me.

31:58.900 --> 32:01.084
Leah: Why were you
and Louis fighting?

32:01.086 --> 32:03.812
Because I know you signed
a big real estate deal

32:03.814 --> 32:05.422
that summer in Edgartown

32:05.424 --> 32:08.483
that put "The Teddy Franklin"
on the map.

32:08.485 --> 32:11.011
That deal was dirty,
wasn't it?

32:12.156 --> 32:13.931
Were you undervaluing
the properties

32:13.933 --> 32:17.342
of poor Black folks
like you are now?

32:17.344 --> 32:19.177
Daddy, is that what
he confronted you about?

32:19.179 --> 32:21.513
Leah --
All summer, you've gone
through great lengths

32:21.515 --> 32:24.833
to secure your legacy
by setting me up for the fall.

32:24.835 --> 32:25.776
That ends tonight.

32:25.927 --> 32:30.096
Daddy, your behavior
then and now is abysmal.

32:30.857 --> 32:33.858
And I am who I am,
but your arrogance

32:33.860 --> 32:36.528
is setting a bad example
for the kids.

32:36.530 --> 32:38.863
I mean, I see
how it affects them.

32:39.774 --> 32:45.020
So I want you out of this house
and Franklin Holdings tonight.

32:45.022 --> 32:47.130
♪♪

32:50.877 --> 32:55.030
♪♪

32:55.032 --> 32:57.032
You know,
in the old days,

32:57.034 --> 33:00.460
the dancing began
at 8:30 sharp.

33:00.462 --> 33:03.221
Back then, we cared
about punctuality.

33:03.223 --> 33:05.148
But under
Leah's direction,

33:05.150 --> 33:07.484
we are firmly
on CP Time.

33:07.486 --> 33:10.378
You know, I doubt that
we will even get through

33:10.380 --> 33:14.324
the inductee ceremony in time
for the "Talented Tenth" photo

33:14.326 --> 33:15.641
at 10:00 P.M. sharp.

33:15.643 --> 33:19.054
It's [scoffs] always been
a time-honored tradition

33:19.056 --> 33:19.997
for the Graceties --

33:19.999 --> 33:22.165
You know, Mama Eve
always taught me

33:22.167 --> 33:25.227
that everyone has
the potential to succeed

33:25.229 --> 33:26.986
if only given
the opportunity.

33:26.988 --> 33:31.082
I mean, this "Talented Tenth"
business is kind of outdated,

33:31.084 --> 33:32.658
and it's divisive.

33:32.660 --> 33:36.096
You know whose idea it was to
blow up all these old pictures?

33:38.166 --> 33:40.091
Mine.
[ Sighs ]

33:40.093 --> 33:44.312
And do you know
what I learned while doing it?

33:45.599 --> 33:51.695
You missed the "Talented Tenth"
photo in 1984.

33:52.923 --> 33:54.698
What happened that night,
Olivia?

33:54.700 --> 33:56.958
Uh, Ruby,
would you mind?

33:56.960 --> 33:59.018
Were you just not
talented enough?

33:59.020 --> 34:02.522
Or were you busy
doing something else --

34:02.524 --> 34:05.858
like putting crack
in my mother's bag

34:05.860 --> 34:08.270
before she drove off
to meet Teddy?

34:08.272 --> 34:14.176
She was arrested at 10:15
driving down to the docks.

34:15.312 --> 34:17.462
Teddy
didn't set her up.

34:17.464 --> 34:20.465
I was looking at the wrong
person the whole time.

34:20.467 --> 34:22.542
You know what, Angela?

34:23.303 --> 34:26.955
Since you're
leaving town and all...

34:26.957 --> 34:29.457
why<i> don't</i> we
get this settled?

34:29.459 --> 34:30.550
Please.

34:30.552 --> 34:31.976
Yes.

34:31.978 --> 34:34.905
I planted the drugs.

34:34.907 --> 34:40.652
Your mother was
a conniving, gold-digging,

34:40.654 --> 34:46.732
social-climbing
home wrecker who crushed --

34:46.734 --> 34:49.978
<i> crushed --</i> my best friend

34:49.980 --> 34:53.998
and destroyed my one chance
at business.

34:54.000 --> 34:56.167
Satisfied?

34:56.169 --> 34:59.096
You have no idea.

34:59.098 --> 35:03.658
'Cause I finally have justice
for my mother.

35:03.660 --> 35:05.660
Justice?

35:05.662 --> 35:07.437
You have no proof.

35:09.257 --> 35:11.424
Actually,
I have every word.

35:11.426 --> 35:14.027
♪♪

35:16.264 --> 35:17.697
[ Screen shatters ]

35:18.600 --> 35:20.617
Oops.
[ Laughs ]

35:20.619 --> 35:22.435
It's in the cloud,
bitch.

35:22.437 --> 35:24.012
You best start thinking about
what you're gonna do

35:24.014 --> 35:26.456
to help me finish
what my mother started.

35:26.458 --> 35:31.795
♪ I remember me,
staring at myself ♪

35:31.797 --> 35:34.038
Leah:
Welcome to the 2021 induction

35:34.040 --> 35:36.133
of the Alpha Chapter
of the Graceties.

35:36.135 --> 35:37.617
Ladies, please approach.

35:37.619 --> 35:42.472
♪ I remember you,
you who I used to be ♪

35:42.474 --> 35:49.554
♪ You still look the same,
but you don't hurt like me ♪

35:49.556 --> 35:54.726
♪ Look at my reflection,
somewhere my affection ♪

35:54.728 --> 36:00.231
♪ Disappeared, isn't here,
nothing left to say ♪

36:00.233 --> 36:05.495
♪ Memories they fading,
but I'm the one who makes them ♪

36:05.497 --> 36:10.408
♪ So I keep the love
close enough to say ♪

36:10.410 --> 36:11.726
♪ What if this life ♪

36:11.728 --> 36:13.561
Like I said
at the beginning of the summer,

36:13.563 --> 36:16.731
many are called
but few are chosen.

36:16.733 --> 36:18.658
♪ We just can't stop living,
scared of what we'll see ♪

36:18.660 --> 36:21.344
And you've all been chosen
to light the path

36:21.346 --> 36:23.905
of our community
through service.

36:23.907 --> 36:26.074
As the President
of the Graceties,

36:26.076 --> 36:27.625
Oak Bluffs Alpha Chapter,

36:27.627 --> 36:30.745
I am proud and would like
to welcome you

36:30.747 --> 36:32.838
into our sacred sisterhood

36:32.840 --> 36:34.891
and conclude
this year's class.

36:34.893 --> 36:36.100
[ Applause ]

36:36.102 --> 36:38.695
♪ I remember me ♪

36:38.697 --> 36:40.846
♪ It don't matter where I go ♪

36:40.848 --> 36:42.848
Welcome to the
sisterhood, sis.

36:42.850 --> 36:44.442
♪ Now you know ♪

36:44.444 --> 36:47.262
♪ I remember me ♪

36:47.264 --> 36:48.263
♪ I remember me ♪

36:48.265 --> 36:49.597
Piggy: She did it, Eve.

36:49.599 --> 36:52.191
She fought tooth and nail
for what was right.

36:52.193 --> 36:55.194
♪ Start to cry, do or die ♪

36:55.196 --> 36:56.771
♪ I remember me ♪

36:56.773 --> 36:58.698
♪ I remember me ♪

36:58.700 --> 37:00.124
Quincy: I don't care
what Ms. Jackie says.

37:00.126 --> 37:03.795
This place and this family
can be...hard,

37:03.797 --> 37:05.055
and you're
the best thing

37:05.057 --> 37:06.723
that's happened to me
all summer.

37:06.725 --> 37:09.117
So we're gonna fight Ms. Jackie
to make her let you stay.

37:09.119 --> 37:11.877
We may not have
to fight too hard, Q.

37:11.879 --> 37:12.971
I'm pregnant.

37:12.973 --> 37:15.123
♪♪

37:15.125 --> 37:17.567
How did you get Olivia
to change her mind?

37:17.569 --> 37:19.294
[ Chuckles ]

37:19.296 --> 37:20.628
♪♪

37:20.630 --> 37:22.130
Turns out...

37:22.132 --> 37:24.799
she was the one
who set up my mother.

37:24.801 --> 37:26.634
Mm-hmm.
I got my answers.

37:26.636 --> 37:30.247
And I want to say I'm sorry
if clearing my mother's name

37:30.249 --> 37:33.065
cost who your mother was
to you.

37:33.067 --> 37:34.659
I'm not sorry.

37:34.661 --> 37:38.237
Now that I know the truth,
I finally understand

37:38.239 --> 37:41.332
what she must have been
going through all those years.

37:41.334 --> 37:44.577
I mean,
my mother's gone,

37:44.579 --> 37:48.122
but...I've never felt
so close to her.

37:48.124 --> 37:49.749
Mm-hmm.

37:49.751 --> 37:52.176
Olivia didn't get off
so easy.

37:52.178 --> 37:55.438
Oh, she didn't.
[ Chuckles ]

37:55.440 --> 37:57.774
Eve's Crown
finally has distribution --

37:57.776 --> 38:01.260
at least, the funds for it --
thanks to a new backer.
What?

38:01.262 --> 38:03.113
Silent, with no power.

38:03.115 --> 38:05.507
[ Laughs ] Wow.

38:05.509 --> 38:07.191
Well, you know,
Olivia's always wanted

38:07.193 --> 38:08.510
to be a businesswoman.

38:08.512 --> 38:11.346
Oh, well, lucky for her,
I am not in the business

38:11.348 --> 38:13.014
of tearing
other women down.

38:13.016 --> 38:18.110
Actually, I'm in the business
of building up our sisters.

38:18.112 --> 38:21.706
Because that is what being
a Gracetie means to me.

38:21.708 --> 38:23.282
Yeah, I actually
said that to you.

38:23.284 --> 38:25.877
I know you said it, bitch.
That's why I said it to you!

38:25.879 --> 38:28.530
[ Both laugh ]

38:28.532 --> 38:32.267
So, does all this mean that
you're staying in Oak Bluffs?

38:33.478 --> 38:34.552
Nate proposed,

38:34.554 --> 38:36.479
wants me to leave
with him tonight.

38:37.799 --> 38:38.706
Whoa.

38:38.708 --> 38:41.133
And Tyrique proposed,
too.

38:41.135 --> 38:42.635
Well, damn.

38:42.637 --> 38:44.228
[ Laughs ]

38:44.230 --> 38:45.655
Well,
where are these rings?

38:45.657 --> 38:48.358
W-What did you say?
I...

38:49.161 --> 38:52.403
I have to talk to both
of them -- in person --

38:52.405 --> 38:54.389
and let them know
what's on my heart.

38:54.391 --> 38:56.649
I'm gonna have to walk away
from one of them.

38:56.651 --> 39:05.900
♪♪

39:05.902 --> 39:11.163
I know you feel as low
as a snake's belly right now...

39:11.165 --> 39:13.183
and you deserve it.

39:13.185 --> 39:16.001
Patricia, have you come
to throw salt on the wound?

39:16.003 --> 39:19.597
Actually,
I came to say...

39:20.433 --> 39:23.693
...thank you,
for loving my sister

39:23.695 --> 39:25.695
even if it was flawed.

39:25.697 --> 39:27.346
And your love for her

39:27.348 --> 39:29.348
perhaps made you
want to help me.

39:29.350 --> 39:31.183
Even if it was twisted,

39:31.185 --> 39:34.245
making me think
that I killed Darius.

39:35.615 --> 39:38.375
But it scared me straight.

39:38.377 --> 39:40.168
Got me clean.

39:41.529 --> 39:43.963
Made me stay clean.

39:46.033 --> 39:48.033
So, what can I say?

39:48.035 --> 39:49.961
You...

39:49.963 --> 39:53.223
saved my life,
Teddy Franklin.

39:53.225 --> 39:56.117
[ Laughs ] Oh, Lord,
looky, looky.

39:56.119 --> 39:58.878
Those words didn't
make me choke.

39:58.880 --> 40:01.231
See, people can change.

40:01.233 --> 40:04.550
You need to change,
Teddy Slick.

40:04.552 --> 40:06.552
Well, Leah wants me
out of the house.

40:06.554 --> 40:08.980
I think that's
a pretty sizable change.

40:08.982 --> 40:11.132
Well, if I know you
like I think I do,

40:11.134 --> 40:13.726
you ain't gonna
just slither away.

40:13.728 --> 40:15.970
Come on, now.
Man up.

40:15.972 --> 40:18.640
You got nine lives,
Teddy.

40:18.642 --> 40:20.733
Well...

40:20.735 --> 40:22.477
here's to nine more.

40:22.479 --> 40:27.649
♪♪

40:27.651 --> 40:28.833
Valet: Mr. Franklin?

40:28.835 --> 40:30.910
Your car is ready.
Mm.

40:30.912 --> 40:40.586
♪♪

40:40.588 --> 40:42.497
[ Door closes ]

40:42.499 --> 40:45.424
♪♪

40:45.426 --> 40:46.851
Oh, hey, Nik.

40:46.853 --> 40:48.461
We're gonna miss
the last ferry.

40:48.463 --> 40:49.762
Where's your mom?
I don't know.

40:49.764 --> 40:51.931
She said she went
to tell Tyrique something.

40:51.933 --> 41:01.532
♪♪

41:01.534 --> 41:03.668
[ Sighs ]

41:06.131 --> 41:07.780
[ Exhales slowly ]

41:08.467 --> 41:11.192
Thanks for letting me down
in person.

41:11.194 --> 41:13.361
What are you
talking about?

41:13.363 --> 41:16.881
I'm saying yes, silly.

41:16.883 --> 41:17.865
You are?

41:17.867 --> 41:20.125
Then why are you crying?

41:20.127 --> 41:22.562
It's just a lot.

41:24.207 --> 41:25.723
But I'm happy.

41:25.725 --> 41:28.467
And I'm excited.

41:28.469 --> 41:30.320
And I'm yours.

41:30.322 --> 41:38.143
♪♪

41:38.145 --> 41:40.312
[ Chuckles ] I am --

41:40.314 --> 41:42.390
I've been in this office
so many times...

41:42.392 --> 41:44.909
Mm-hmm.
...but it just feels
different.

41:44.911 --> 41:46.060
Different?
Mm-hmm.

41:46.062 --> 41:49.731
Okay, well, I have
a few different things

41:49.733 --> 41:52.066
I'd like to try
on this desk.

41:52.068 --> 41:53.568
Ooh, well,
I've got a position

41:53.570 --> 41:56.420
I'm pretty sure
you're gonna love.

41:56.422 --> 42:00.016
♪♪

42:00.018 --> 42:03.244
As the new Chairman
of Franklin Holdings and Darmon,

42:03.246 --> 42:05.004
effectively immediately.

42:05.006 --> 42:06.264
Nah.
[ Laughs ]

42:06.266 --> 42:08.024
But all this was
supposed to be yours.

42:08.026 --> 42:10.434
